<DocsLayout
  title="Installation"
  description="Install the Shuttle CLI and set up your environment"
  section="Getting Started"
>
  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <p>Before installing Shuttle, make sure you have the following on your local machine:</p>

  <h3>Bun runtime</h3>
  <p>
    Shuttle is built with Bun. Install it with the official installer:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash</code></pre>
  <p>
    Verify the installation:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">bun --version
# 1.1.0 or newer</code></pre>

  <h3>Docker</h3>
  <p>
    Shuttle builds Docker images locally and transfers them to the server. You need Docker
    Desktop (macOS/Windows) or Docker Engine (Linux) installed and running.
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">docker --version
# Docker version 26.x or newer</code></pre>

  <h3>SSH key pair</h3>
  <p>
    Shuttle connects to your VPS over SSH using public key authentication. If you do not
    already have an SSH key pair, generate one:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "shuttle-deploy"
# Your public key: ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub</code></pre>
  <p>
    Copy your public key to the target server. The user you deploy as must have
    <code>sudo</code> access (or be <code>root</code>) for the initial provisioning step.
    After provisioning, a dedicated <code>deploy</code> system user is created.
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">ssh-copy-id deploy@YOUR_SERVER_IP</code></pre>

  <h2>Install Shuttle</h2>

  <h3>Global install (recommended)</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">bun add -g shuttle-deploy</code></pre>
  <p>This installs the <code>shuttle</code> binary globally and makes it available in your <code>PATH</code>.</p>

  <h3>Project-local install</h3>
  <p>
    If you prefer to pin the version per project, add it as a dev dependency:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">bun add -d shuttle-deploy</code></pre>
  <p>
    Then invoke it via <code>bunx shuttle</code> or add scripts to your <code>package.json</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-json">&#123;
  "scripts": &#123;
    "deploy": "shuttle deploy",
    "provision": "shuttle provision"
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Verify the installation</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle --version
# shuttle 0.x.x</code></pre>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle --help</code></pre>
  <p>You should see the full command list including <code>init</code>, <code>provision</code>, <code>deploy</code>, and others.</p>

  <h2>Server requirements</h2>
  <p>
    The target VPS must meet the following requirements before running <code>shuttle provision</code>:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Debian 11+ or Ubuntu 22.04+ (64-bit)</li>
    <li>Minimum 1 GB RAM (2 GB recommended)</li>
    <li>SSH access with a user that has <code>sudo</code> privileges</li>
    <li>Ports 22, 80, and 443 open on the firewall</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The <code>shuttle provision</code> command will install Docker, Caddy, and configure UFW
    automatically. You do not need to pre-install anything on the server.
  </p>

  <h2>Shell completion</h2>
  <p>
    Shell completion support is planned for a future release. Watch the
    <a href="https://github.com/shuttle-hq/shuttle" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a>
    for updates.
  </p>

